headline: The Trade War Has Crushed Transportation Companies, But This Dividend-Paying Value Stock Could Still Win
summary: Union Pacific is well-positioned to deliver good results despite tariff uncertainty.  The company has an impressive track record of handling economic slowdowns, thanks to its high margins and return on invested capital.  Union Pacific returns a boatload of capital to shareholders through dividends and buybacks.
